{"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/atprotokit\/0210authflowchange"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit"]]},"metadata":{"title":"0.21 to 0.26 Authentication Flow Migration","role":"article","modules":[{"name":"ATProtoKit"}],"roleHeading":"Article"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn about how to set up your project with the new authentication flow changes."}],"kind":"article","sections":[],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/0210AuthFlowChange"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"With the release of 0.26.0 comes a new migration flow for ATProtoKit developers. This change is fairly small, but this article will still cover what to expect in order to clear any confusion.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Authentication Flow","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Authentication-Flow"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Previously, when you wanted to authenticate to an AT Protocol service, you used an initializer from ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration"},{"text":", which contained the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"handle"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"password"},{"type":"text","text":" parameters. Then, you would use ATProtocolConfiguration.authenticate(authenticationFactorToken:) and passed the instance to the "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtoKit","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"class"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["let config = ATProtocolConfiguration(handle: example.bsky.social, password: hunter2)","","Task {","    do {","        \/\/ You can put it in here…","        try await config.authenticate()","","        let atProto = ATProtoKit(sessionConfiguration: config)","","        \/\/ Or here…","        try await config.authenticate()","    } catch {","        throw error","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"With version 0.26, this has been changed slightly:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["let config = ATProtocolConfiguration()","","Task {","    do {","","        let atProto = ATProtoKit(sessionConfiguration: config)","","        \/\/ Enter the handle and password in here.","        try await config.authenticate(","            handle: example.bsky.social,","            password: hunter2","        )","    } catch {","        throw error","    }","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Here are the changes being made:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration"},{"type":"text","text":"’s initializer no longer takes the "},{"code":"handle","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"code":"password","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" parameters: now, ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/authenticate(with:password:)","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" is responsible.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This is the only external change. However, more has been made internally:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/UserSession","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" is no longer stored inside of "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":": now, a new "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"actor"},{"type":"text","text":" named "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/UserSessionRegistry","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" holds all instances of the ","type":"text"},{"code":"struct","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"code":"UUID","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" value has been added to the "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"class"},{"text":". This value is linked to all objects that are related to the session. This is part of the new initializer for ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration","isActive":true},{"text":", named ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/init(pdsURL:keychainProtocol:configuration:canResolve:)","isActive":true},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration"},{"text":" now closely follows ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SessionConfiguration"},{"type":"text","text":". In fact, the following methods are no longer stored in the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"class"},{"type":"text","text":", but have moved to default implementations of the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"protocol"},{"text":":","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/authenticate(with:password:)","type":"reference","isActive":true}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/getSession()","isActive":true}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/refreshSession()","type":"reference","isActive":true}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/deleteSession()","type":"reference"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A new "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"protocol"},{"type":"text","text":", named "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SecureKeychainProtocol"},{"type":"text","text":", will now manage the management of the password, access token, and refresh token. An "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"actor"},{"type":"text","text":", named "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/AppleSecureKeychain","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" is available for applications running on Apple’s platforms."}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","text":"`SessionConfiguration`","level":2,"anchor":"SessionConfiguration"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"As mentioned previously, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SessionConfiguration"},{"text":" now has default configurations for each of the required methods. It is also ","type":"text"},{"code":"Sendable","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and requires a ","type":"text"},{"code":"class","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to conform to it. The default implementation assumes you’re using an App Password to authenticate by default, but you’re able to create new implementations for your own conforming "},{"code":"class","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Furthermore, the ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SessionConfiguration\/authenticate(with:password:)-272a8","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" method handles Two-Factor Authentication, but the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"protocol"},{"text":" can also handle OAuth. This is thanks to a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"AsyncStream"},{"type":"text","text":"-related properties, named "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SessionConfiguration\/codeContinuation","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SessionConfiguration\/codeStream"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"level":2,"text":"Auto-managing the Keychain","type":"heading","anchor":"Auto-managing-the-Keychain"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"As mentioned earlier, a new ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"protocol"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"actor","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" have been made: "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SecureKeychainProtocol"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/AppleSecureKeychain"},{"text":" respectively. This manages the keychain items for the password and refresh token, as well as storing the access token in-memory.","type":"text"}]},{"name":"Note","style":"note","type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The access token is being stored in-memory due to how frequently the token expires.","type":"text"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/AppleSecureKeychain","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" conforms to ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SecureKeychainProtocol","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" and is the default object used for Apple platforms. It’s also the default object used when initializing with "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration","type":"reference"},{"text":". However, you’re free to create your own implementation if it doesn’t suit your needs.","type":"text"}]},{"style":"note","type":"aside","name":"Note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"At this time, Linux and Windows developers will need to implement their own ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"actor"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"class"},{"type":"text","text":" to achieve the same effect. However, default "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"actor"},{"type":"text","text":"s for those platforms will be created at a later date."}]}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"references":{"doc://ATProtoKit/documentation/ATProtoKit/SecureKeychainProtocol":{"abstract":[{"text":"A protocol for managing the keychain in an AT Protcol account.","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"SecureKeychainProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/atprotokit\/securekeychainprotocol","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SecureKeychainProtocol","role":"symbol","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"SecureKeychainProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"SecureKeychainProtocol"},"doc://ATProtoKit/documentation/ATProtoKit/ATProtocolConfiguration/init(pdsURL:keychainProtocol:configuration:canResolve:)":{"role":"symbol","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/init(pdsURL:keychainProtocol:configuration:canResolve:)","fragments":[{"kind":"iden